1. Who invaded the Kingdom of Israel in 722 BC?
The Assyrians
2. What was the capital city of the Kingdom of Judea?
Jerusalem
3. What happened in 586 BC in Judea?
The Babylonians conquered the Judea. 
4. When the Jews returned to Judea what did they then set out to do?
They set out to restore the Jews, rebuild temples, and restore their religion basically. 
5. What happened to Judea in 334?
Alexander the Great of Macedon conquered the Achaemenid Empire and Judea
6. Who was next to conquer this region?
The romans
7. What could have been another consequence of all this turmoil in the land of Israel?
The deaths of all the Jews, and the loss of knowledge. 
